commit.message: Switch the dependency back to rbtree
Bump the version to 1.0.2 and update documents
Use the rbtree3 gem which builds with Ruby HEAD

Be a no-op library for JRuby

JRuby has its own (optimized) version of Set and SortedSet, and they
haven't yet removed SortedSet from the standard library.

Undefine SortedSet before defining it

This is necessary to avoid circualr require with set >=1.0.0 and
incomplete implementation override with Ruby 2.x.
Allow a failure with ruby-head which needs to be updated
Add a test workflow for GitHub

Import the initial version of sorted_set as a gem

This version requires RBTree as the internal storage.
